               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170702-63-person536">
                  ESTHER 
                  LEATHARD
               <interp inst="t18170702-63-person536" type="surname" value="LEATHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170702-63-person536" type="given" value="ESTHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170702-63-person536" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Giles Leathard. On the 2d of June, about half-past ten o'clock at night, as I was going home with my husband, we had just got to our house, my husband went on to get the door open, the prisoner came behind me, and snatched my shawl off-it was not fastened-it was gone in a minute. I fell down with fear, and made no resistance - He did not throw me down. I gave the alarm.</p>
               <p>GILES LEATHARD. I am the husband of the last witness. I ran after the prisoner, and secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170702-63-person537">
                  THOMAS 
                  HAYCOCK
               <interp inst="t18170702-63-person537" type="surname" value="HAYCOCK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170702-63-person537" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170702-63-person537" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was given into my charge. I searched him. The shawl dropped out of his hat.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 20.</p>
